g.text: You: Attempt to stop *The Expression* from happening.
You: No one tells me what to do.
Encyclopedia: For Revachol -- your city -- that meant only one thing: Guillaume Le Million!
Forget about Ostentatious Orchestrations. For Revachol -- your city -- that meant only one thing: Guillaume Le Million!
Mirror: Whatever it is, at least it's dead now. There's clearly rigor mortis on your face. Or wait... is that an *expression*? Are you trying to make an expression with that face?
You: I have no idea why it's there. It just is.
Mirror: Maybe that's how it started? And now it doesn't even matter anymore -- you've worn that grin into your face and it will never come *off*...
Mirror: What does it even *mean*? What is the emotion you're trying to convey?
Volition: You couldn't stop if you wanted to. It's neurological.
You: Actually, I'm not sure I *can* stop.
Mirror: Good call. Go ahead and try something, if you like. Or -- you know -- stop staring into the mirror.
You: No, this is what superstars do. (Keep making the face.)
Mirror: You should check yourself for a pulse, because from here it looks like a cadaverous spasm.
Shivers: In a rundown shack on the far coast, a middle-aged man pounds his fist and looses an animal cry as he stares into a sliver of clouded glass...
You: I don't think I can do that.
Endurance: It was time to banish that ridiculous *Expression* from your face -- and replace it with a perfect reflection of your unyielding resolve, your noble suffering.
Endurance: Look deep inside yourself. You know it's true, because it *hurts*.
Endurance: It takes a true kingsman to summon the *will* to face reality in all its darkness. To stare straight into the abyss and do *what must be done*.
Endurance: This idiocy has gone on too long. It's time to wipe that decadent homo-sexual grin off your face.
You: It was just a reflex!
Endurance: The problem is obvious: You simply can't hack it. You're a failure. It's all *too much* for you.
Mirror: The bathroom mirror has been wiped completely clean. You see the reflection of your face in the mirror -- such as it is without *The Expression*. It's just hairy.
You: I don't care. (Still wipe the mirror.)
I don't care, I hurt myself, it's what I do. (Wipe the mirror.)
You: I think it might be because I'm a superstar.

Mirror: Really -- all recollection of the person you are, the people in your life and even the world you're in has drowned in a sea of blood alcohol. This was no mere night of drinking, it was a deluge. Of world-ending proportions.
Inland Empire: Abort! You clearly have not thought this through. You won't like what you will see there -- and you will never *un-become* it.
You: Lets just get it over with. Wipe the mirror.
You: Maybe I should touch it first, make sure there's nothing *wrong* with my face.
You: I'm scared. I want to stop doing this.
Inland Empire: No-no, not the voice! Make it stop...

Endurance: While the world burns, the two of you, together again, ride an aerostatic into the sunset. Maybe it will work this time? Spare Revachol and you'll never hear from her again. Will you sacrifice a second chance at love to keep Revachol safe?
You: Wait, what happened to my face?
Endurance: You're a hard motherfucker... (Tightness -- in gaseous form -- leaves your body.) If we didn't know better, we'd say you *enjoyed* consigning your city to the flames.
Endurance: Now open your eyes and witness the wonder! The HMS Last Kingsman has left the docks. The world will tremble as you smash all the ice in the world.
Endurance: It's time. Time to see yourself as you truly are. It's going to be absolutely *devastating*, but there's no way to avoid it.
Encyclopedia: Like the rest of you, it comes from a bad place somewhere in the past. That's all you know for now.
Endurance: It's time. Time to see yourself as you truly are. It's going to be absolutely *devastating*, but there's no way to avoid it.
Endurance: It turns out you've already been wearing your *true* face. The face of The Loser. The face of He Who Could Not Handle It. Now, get out of your sight.
Composure: *Ahem*. It's a *lot* like the face on that rather unfortunate muscle-man t-shirt you just so happen to be wearing...
Electrochemistry: Just like that it's over -- the running gag that your life had become. A sad old man looks back at you.
Mirror: You *can't*, can you? It's like it's not even voluntary anymore. You have worn that grin into your face and now it won't come *off*...
Mirror: Don't be scared. It's only your face. It's not like anyone is going to *see* it.
Encyclopedia: Sometimes you like to add finger pistols to the mix, because unlike Guillaume le Million you are a police officer. It's your nifty little way to say: I'm armed and dangerous.

Encyclopedia: There is a vast ocean of time between right now and *The Expression* looking good on you -- or anyone. Two decades, if the calendar is to be trusted. Humanity has run aground in that time, it's a different world now. The Expression is a relic.
Encyclopedia: You have some understanding of the recent history of disco. The rest is darkness.
You have some understanding of the near history of disco. The rest is darkness, aside from the useless fact that the motor carriage outside was a Coupris Kineema.
Mirror: Oh my god, you *can't* stop! It's like it's not even voluntary anymore! You have worn that grin into your face and now it won't come off...
Endurance: Can't hear you over the moans of your w√∂men. They writhe in pleasure as the foreigners are playing them like instruments. Be careful, or they'll wear you like a sock, Harry.
You: Wait, why do I need to do that?
Endurance: *Nothing* -- not pain, fatigue, hunger, fear or desire -- will ever deviate you from the path. Like an icebreaker you crush all opposition, ploughing forward *no matter what it takes*.
You: What's going on? I thought I *succeeded*!
Endurance: This idiocy has gone on far too long. It's time to wipe that decadent homo-sexual grin off your face. Time to see yourself as you truly are.
Endurance: Love... time... Revachol... all of it. The pressure is putting you on your knees.
You: It's never not too late! I can *still* turn it back...
Endurance: No, it's *far* too late. All that remains is for you to feel bad, because you failed, and there's nothing you can do about it. That is the way of the world...
Endurance: Yes. It *should* be awful, because you failed. Failing is weakness and weakness is awful. That is the way of the world...
Electrochemistry: It's like something snaps in you -- a nerve ending, a thought, a sadness. Your face in the mirror is suddenly clean of the leer that had distorted it for god knows how long.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. It's barely covered in steam anymore. You see your face, such as it is. A regular, clean-shaven police officer.
Electrochemistry: It's like something snaps in you -- a nerve ending, a thought, a sadness. Your face in the mirror is suddenly clean of the leer that had distorted it. For god knows how long...
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. In it -- your face, adorned with *The Expression*.
Mirror: A mirror hangs above a bent and broken sink. In a fierce discharge of masculine energy someone has ripped half the faucet off.
You: It's an expression of pain.
You: [Let the mirror be for now.]
Mirror: You liar. You can't even tell the truth to yourself. Go ahead, try something!
You: No way, I'm not doing this. [Back off.]

Encyclopedia: Out of the dazzling swirl of disco music, in an open air *bo√Æte de nuit* somewhere in Revachol West, Guillaume's blond mane appeared on the screen. He sang some bullshit. Then he made *The Expression*.
Electrochemistry: With all the synapses you extinguished, it's a miracle you can even think this sentence. You've interrupted a true act of self-annulment here.
You: Anything else? Like who am I? Why did I drink myself into oblivion?
Anything else? Like who am I? Why did I become a cop? Why did I drink myself into oblivion?
Endurance: The bloated whores, schizophrenic anarchists and deformed moneylenders tremble, trying to shield their eyes, as he -- *Le gendarme en diamant* -- walks by!
You: I may as well give up then...
Endurance: Who said anything about giving up?
Endurance: Enough. The Franconigerian Court of Honour has held your naked soul up against the Sevenfold Sun Miracle and looked right through it. Close your eyes and *know*, this is who you are:
Electrochemistry: Hey! It took a minor neurological *miracle* to get your face to this point!
Endurance: You don't even have anything to say for yourself, do you? Just gonna take it all lying down? Why not grab your ankles while you're at it? That's why you never stood a chance.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. It's barely covered in steam anymore. You see yourself -- *The Expression* fixed to your clean-shaven face. You're still not accustomed to it.
You: Of course I do. It's... uhm... is it some kind of superstar? I think I'm a superstar.
Mirror: It appears you're also dead. There's clearly rigor mortis on your face, or wait... is that an *expression*? Are you trying to make an expression with that face? Why?
You: God, I don't know -- it's indescribable.
You: How bad could it be?
You: I think it's supposed to look *suggestive*. I'm afraid it's meant *for the ladies*.
Drama: If it doesn't rhyme, you're not pronouncing it right.
You: How long ago was The New?
Mirror: It doesn't have to be. You can swoon over Guillaume and his champagne-cork smile whenever you want to... Maybe some of the stardust will return?
You: I can try to. (Try to stop.)
You: Hold on, my cocksmanship is on par with...!
Shivers: From above the Bay of Revachol, a cold wind gathers in response. The people of the fishing village pull their coats and blankets tight about themselves...
Endurance: *Never*. May this serve as a constant reminder of your sacred, un-put-downable burthen.
Inland Empire: You are a terror even to yourself!
Volition: Does this thing *unmake* you, or does it heal you?
Encyclopedia: Nine million souls flicker out of existence. Sixteen if you include the greater metropolitan area.
Endurance: Have you really been wearing that decadent homo-sexual grin this whole time? It's disgusting. No wonder you haven't been able to *truly face yourself*.
Esprit de Corps: He sets down the paper and quickly scribbles the date and time in his notebook, along with a note: 'HDB possible relapse? Check in first thing.'
Endurance: Now shout from the top of your lungs: YOU ARE THE NOBLE SUFFERER.

Endurance: Now, every night, while you masturbate in the ruins of your not-so-great-anymore hall, they're getting pleasured by foreign men with superior testosterone levels and *far* more advanced sexual practices than your feeble grunt-and-thrust.
You: I don't want to know.
Encyclopedia: The click is used to spur on a horse. It also features heavily in Guillaume Le Million's regional mega-hit "Don't Worry (Your Pretty Little Head)".
Endurance: A day will come when you need to take a shotgun to that cellar, shoot whatever is down there in the head, and walk away, never looking back.
Shivers: A cold damp seeps in through the gaps between the wall planks. There is no one to bear witness to your vow...
You: (Bow down.) Yes. My heart forever beats for Revachol, I am all she has left. The constant kingsman.
You: What happens to me then?
Endurance: Face it, br√∂ther. No one's got the *willpower* to set things right. They won't do what it takes.

Endurance: You will be free to love Revachol like no one has ever loved her. You will be her champion, and she will be *faithful* to you. If you can just make this last sacrifice, you will *finally* know happiness.

Endurance: Now open your eyes and witness the (small) wonder! The HMS Modest Kingsman has left the docks. You are neither the greatest nor the strongest icebreaker on the seas, but you are what you are.
Endurance: It's time. Time to see yourself as you truly are. It's going to be absolutely *devastating*, but there's no way to avoid it.
Endurance: This idiocy has gone on too long. It's time to wipe that decadent homo-sexual grin off your face.
Endurance: It's time. Your efforts at avoiding this moment have been truly *heroic*, but now there's nothing left but for you to confront yourself as you *truly* are, no matter the consequences...
Interfacing: The faucet is quite terribly mangled, but you just might be able to twist its parts into place.
Interfacing: You handle the chaincutters deftly, applying just enough pressure. The faucet regains a recognizable shape. The steam stops.
Mirror: An old mirror hangs on the wall. You see the reflection of your face in it -- such as it is without *The Expression*. It's just hairy.
Conceptualization: Was this not the same *√©lan* that founds empires and lays waste to cities, virile, uncaring towards *the little things*?
Electrochemistry: It's too late. Like an image on film, *The Expression* belongs to your primary motor cortex. It would take a minor neurological miracle for you to cease producing it.
You: I'm pretty sure I can't stop.
Authority: This is the face worn by the first law-bringers, the noble tyrants. Today you join their number...
Conceptualization: You'll plough your way toward the frigid lands of Katla and Vaasa, smashing every ice sheet in your path. Nothing, *nothing* can stop an icebreaker...
Interfacing: Told you that you *needed* those chaincutters. Everything is connected. Everything has a purpose.
Endurance: This idiocy has gone on too long. It's time to wipe that decadent homo-sexual grin off your face.
Endurance: Yes, you did. There's no use denying it...
Endurance: Let this new face be a reminder, an unalterable mark of shame. This is the face of The Loser, the face of He Who Looks at Himself and Despairs. Now, get out of your sight.
Endurance: It wasn't enough. You simply don't have what it *takes*...
Volition: Maybe it will make you temptation-proof, so something good will come out of this at least?
Mirror: It's not. It's swollen and snail-like, wriggling between your fingers.
You: I guess that's it then. (Conclude.)
Mirror: You have no idea who this *thing* is, do you?
Mirror: There might have been. Ten years ago. It's little more than a cadaverous spasm now.
Mirror: Oh my god, you're right! It's like it's not even voluntary anymore. You have worn that grin into your face and now it won't come *off*...
Endurance: Fine... The three of you, all together, ride an aerostatic into the sunset. The question remains: Will you sacrifice love to keep Revachol safe?

Endurance: We keep it buried like a horrible secret. We feed it through the cracks in the floorboards out of a sickening sense of nostalgia. Just enough to keep it alive. And yet it still comes to us in moments of weakness, unbidden, a source of shame and panic...
Endurance: Face it, br√∂ther. No one's got the *willpower* to build her up again. They won't do what has to be done.
Endurance: There's a lever in front of you. Pull it, and atomic fire blankets your beloved Revachol. Millions die in an instant. But you are spared. You, and the voice in the payphone.
You: I will never forsake my v√∂ws. (Conclude.)
Endurance: Despite doubt, fear, sentimentality and weakness, you plough ever forward, like an icebreaker, tearing through the frigid North Sea.
You: But I was trying so hard! I was making progress!
Endurance: Oh yes, they're all gone. Carried off by foreign invaders because you failed to uphold your most ancient and noble v√∂ws. The worst part is they might even *prefer* it this way...

Encyclopedia: It belongs in The New -- the third decade of the current century. Enough time had passed from the failure of Revolution that, for a fleeting moment, free market economy seemed like the ultimate, uncontested way of life for our species.
Mirror: *Too* late. You clearly have rigor mortis on your face, or wait... is that an *expression*? Are you trying to make an expression with that face? Why?
You: Does this have anything to do with Ostentatious Orchestrations?
You: Will I ever be able to make another face again?
Pain Threshold: That voice... so warm and sweet...
Esprit de Corps: You used to believe you came from a large family with many half-brothers and sisters, but where are they now? However you shout, they can't hear you...
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. In it -- your face, a regular, clean-shaven police officer.
Mirror: An old mirror hangs on the wall. You see the reflection of your face in it -- adorned with *The Expression*.

Encyclopedia: Things were good. It was *smooth sailing*. People made gold-and-champagne-tinted interiors and fa√ßades to suit the times, calling this *The New Style*. But, more importantly -- disco happened.
Mirror: You should check yourself for a pulse, superstar. From here it looks like a cadaverous spasm.
Encyclopedia: Everyone loved it. Maybe you thought some of the stardust would rub off on you? Maybe it did? Either way, it's all gone now. Only the grimace remains.
You: I don't need to. I almost died trying to get that tie, but I heard my heart beat.
Mirror: That's right! Not even yourself. Go ahead, try something, it's not an order.
Conceptualization: This is a horrible allegory for... whatever is on the other end.
Endurance: It was time to banish that pitiful, *sad* look from your face -- and replace it with a perfect reflection of your unyielding resolve, your noble suffering.
Interfacing: An involuntary twitch runs through your hand, almost like reflex.
Mirror: You step back from the mirror. A bead of water drips from the pipe beneath the washbasin.
Mirror: The mirror begins to clear slowly without you having to wipe it.
Mirror: The bathroom mirror has been wiped completely clean. You see the reflection of your face in the mirror -- even now adorned with *The Expression*.
Mirror: Where to even begin? There's the bloatedness, then the swollenness... It's like there's an upholstery of alcohol underneath your skin.

Mirror: Bet you are. Your nose feels like a small balloon in the middle of your face. It hurts when you honk it, and it doesn't appear to be a particularly tiny nose either. Not with all the drinks it's *absorbed* for you.

It's not, your nose feels like a balloon in the middle of your face. It hurts when you honk it -- doesn't appear to be a particularly small nose either. Not with all the drinks it's *absorbed* for you.
You: Dig deep into your mind to locate the source of *The Expression*.

Encyclopedia: Some twenty odd years. There is a vast ocean of time between right now and *The Expression* looking good on you -- or anyone. Humanity has run aground in that time, it's a different world now. The Expression is a relic.
Mirror: No. That would be too insane.
Encyclopedia: *Ahem*. It's *very* similar to the face Hjelmdallermann is always making on the cover of those books...
Endurance: What's that? Can't hear yourself over the moans of your w√∂men in the hands of foreigners who play them like instruments. Be careful, or they'll wear you like a sock, Harry-boy.
Composure: *Ahem*. It's a *lot* like the face a certain muscle-man is making on that t-shirt you insist on carrying around...
Endurance: It's time you knew the truth, br√∂ther.
You: How dare you speak of Revachol that way...
Endurance: Yes... you truly are. (Tightness -- in gaseous form -- leaves your body.) She's lucky to have you, watching her sleep.
Esprit de Corps: He sighs and returns to his crossword. He is a police officer, not a baby-sitter.
You: I won't give up. I *can't* give up.
Endurance: Look at yourself: You go about with this mopey look on your face like a dog who's been beaten with an old stick.
Interfacing: Your hands, however skilful, can't manage this task on their own. You should get your chaincutters out.
You: This is the face of a late-stage alcoholic.
Mirror: Getting clever appears to make *The Expression* even worse. Now it's mixed with smugness.
Electrochemistry: Still not happening. It won't come off that easy.
Mirror: Suddenly you realise you have no memory of the face that awaits you there, underneath the soft vapour.

Endurance: Remember: Kingsmen are not born, they are made. And the only thing that can unmake us is that which drove us to rise above in the first place. We keep that thing locked in the deepest cellars of our mind. So deep we forget what it is.
Mirror: Please promise yourself you are not going to try it on any of the *ladies*, whatever happens.
Endurance: So ask yourself, when the time comes, can you shoot the past in the head, walk away, and never look back on its rotting remains?
Endurance: You're tired, afraid, sad, hungry and in pain. But most of all: confused. Yet *still*, like a tiny icebreaker -- the tiniest boat in the fleet -- you plough ever forward...
Endurance: What was *that*? Did you just *flinch* before your own reflection?
You: I'm insinuating that I'm vaguely sympathetic. I think I'm sort of pulling it off too -- in a *sad has-been* kind of way. There is some charm to it.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. It's barely covered in steam anymore. It's your face in the mirror -- adorned with *The Expression*.
Mirror: Please stop, it's horrible! You're scaring yourself.
Physical Instrument: That's one way of saying that the nerve damage is *quite* severe. The only way you'll be able to change your face now is with your fingers...
You: (Rack the imaginary shotgun.) Whatever it takes. For *Revachol*.
You: Accept your fate with quiet resignation.
Endurance: It can, and it *is*. Just a mountain of shit, every bit of it.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. In it -- your clean-shaven face, adorned with *The Expression*. You're still not accustomed to it.
Mirror: An old mirror hangs on the wall. You see your reflection in it -- *The Expression* fixed to your clean-shaven face. You're still not accustomed to it.
Mirror: Hot water sprays from the base and steam covers the mirror. You cannot see yourself, just the outline of a man.
Hot water sprays from the faucet's base and steam covers the mirror. You cannot see yourself, just a vague impression of a man.
You: At least my tongue is okay. (Touch your tongue.)
Mirror: You step back from the mirror. A loose board creaks.
You: How do I know I'm a true kingsman?
Endurance: It's time. Time to see yourself as you truly are. It's going to be absolutely *devastating*, but there's no way to avoid it.
You: God, does it have to be so awful?
Endurance: And that doesn't even *begin* to cover what's happened to your w√∂men...
You: Use your chaincutters to fix the faucet. Stop steam from fogging up the mirror.
Interfacing: The chaincutters slip out of your hands as you attempt to twist the faucet into place. Well, you know one thing for sure -- you've probably never been a plumber.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. In it -- your face, now without *The Expression*. It's just hairy.
Mirror: An old mirror hangs on the wall. You see the reflection of your face in it -- such as it is. A regular clean-shaven police officer.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the wall, covered in steam. You cannot see yourself, just the outlines of a man. You have no memory of the face that awaits you there, underneath the soft vapour.
You: So I adopted it? Why?
You: I feel the need to add a clicking sound when I make it: *Click-click*.
You: If I can't stop, I wouldn't want to know. Better to just keep making it.
You: You're wrong. There's still a way to turn back time. To make things *richtig*.
I'm sure everything is fine. (Touch your nose.)

Endurance: That stupid *Expression* was your last line of defence, but now even that has collapsed. The combined armies of Pain and Shit are streaming through your gates, pillaging your stores, carrying off your w√∂men...
Endurance: You've let your guard down. Now the combined armies of Pain and Shit are streaming through your gates, pillaging your stores, carrying off your w√∂men...
You: Dear lord help me, what is this?!
Encyclopedia: Not really. OO must have just stirred your mind. They're more like a disco rock band anyway...

Esprit de Corps: Meanwhile, his colleague is filling in the last clues of his nightly crossword when he hears what seems to be some kind of animalistic howling from the adjoining room. He directs his eyes toward the door of their shared bathroom...
Esprit de Corps: In a mould-covered bathroom inside a trashed hostel near the edge of Martinaise, a middle-aged man grips the sides of a cold sink in white-knuckled fury...
You: I will bear any burthen.
Endurance: Your heart can belong to Revachol or it can belong to darkness. As long as it's torn between them it's broken and useless.
Interfacing: Told you that you *needed* those chaincutters. Everything is connected. Everything has a purpose.
Mirror: A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall. It's barely covered in steam anymore. You see your face, such as it is without *The Expression*. It's just hairy.
Mirror: Yeah, there is definitely something wrong with it.
Mirror: As you slowly reach your hand toward the surface of the mirror...
Endurance: You haven't yet banished all weakness, but you will. We know you will...
You: Wait, can Kim be in the aerostatic too?
Mirror: You should check yourself for a pulse, superstar. From here it looks like a cadaverous spasm.

Endurance: Oh yes, they're all *wiped out*. Your bushels of grain, your salted meats, your hogsheads brimming with bitter ale. All gone. Your fields have been put to the torch, your great-hall is a ravaged husk. You are bereft.
You: I'm not making it, the face is making it itself.
Mirror: The bathroom mirror has been wiped completely clean. You see the reflection of yourself in the mirror -- *The Expression* fixed to your clean-shaven face. You're still not accustomed to it.
Mirror: You find no sign of life on your swollen neck. However, putting your hand on your chest reveals an irregular heartbeat. You appear to be alive -- for now.
Endurance: Especially love, br√∂ther. Face it, no one's willing to make the sacrifices that are necessary, not in this day and age.
Mirror: An old mirror hangs on the wall, half-covered in shadows. You cannot see yourself fully, just the outline of a man. You have no memory of the face that awaits you there.

Encyclopedia: You have some understanding of the near history of disco, plus the trivia you've picked up along the way. Episodic memory, however, remains in the dark. It may never return. You should prepare yourself for that.
Mirror: The bathroom mirror has been wiped completely clean. You see the reflection of your face in the mirror -- such as it is. A regular, clean-shaven police officer.
